<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Auto Backup rules (Android < 12, API < 31). The newer
  data_extraction_rules.xml takes precedence on Android 12+.

  Policy: backup nothing user-keyed. The earlier policy tried to
  preserve userId across uninstall so reinstall would land back in
  the same account — but the Vouchflow deviceToken (which is what
  actually proves identity) is correctly excluded for security, so
  the userId-only resurrection produces a broken half-state: the JS
  side restores userId from AsyncStorage, SpeakeasyDb can't open
  without the matching cachedDeviceToken, biometric prompt fails,
  identity gets cleared — but the AsyncStorage-restored conversation
  list survives, so the user finishes onboarding as a new id with
  ghost conversations from their prior identity. Reported in the
  rc.79 test cycle (tester9 → reinstall → tester13 saw tester9's
  conversation with @lunchbox8).

  Excluded for security (unchanged):
    - databases/speakeasy.db (+ -journal/-wal/-shm): Signal SQLCipher
      encrypted store. Backing this up to Google Drive (even encrypted)
      crosses the spec §1 trust boundary.
    - sharedpref/vouchflow*.xml: device-bound attestation must not
      cross devices.

  Excluded to fix the rc.79 ghost-identity bug:
    - databases/RKStorage(+-journal): @react-native-async-storage v2's
      SQLite-backed AsyncStorage. Holds @speakeasy/identity, /conversations,
      /profiles, /groups, /settings, etc.
    - files/RKStorage: file-backed AsyncStorage path used on some v2
      configurations; excluded defensively.
    - sharedpref/RCTAsyncLocalStorage*.xml: legacy filename if any
      stragglers survived an AsyncStorage version bump.

  Net effect: reinstall = full re-onboard. Same posture as Signal/
  WhatsApp. Users who want to "land back in their account" need to
  use the (future) handle-recovery flow, which goes through the
  identity-recovery server probe, not Android Auto Backup.
-->
<full-backup-content>
  <exclude domain="database" path="speakeasy.db" />
  <exclude domain="database" path="speakeasy.db-journal" />
  <exclude domain="database" path="speakeasy.db-wal" />
  <exclude domain="database" path="speakeasy.db-shm" />
  <exclude domain="sharedpref" path="vouchflow_attestation.xml" />
  <exclude domain="sharedpref" path="vouchflow.xml" />
  <exclude domain="database" path="RKStorage" />
  <exclude domain="database" path="RKStorage-journal" />
  <exclude domain="file" path="RKStorage" />
  <exclude domain="sharedpref" path="RCTAsyncLocalStorage.xml" />
  <exclude domain="sharedpref" path="RCTAsyncLocalStorage_V1.xml" />
</full-backup-content>
